Title: The Night Shift
Credit: written by
Author: brehon
Source: generated from a metaphor DAG

# ACT ONE

INT. PELL SCIENCE HALL - LOBBY - EVENING

At six, the last of them file out, and the building becomes WALT's.

He holds the door. Forty-one of them go through. The forty-second thanks the door.

INT. PELL SCIENCE HALL - MAIN CORRIDOR - NIGHT

He runs the buffer until the corridor comes up shining and his own face moves in the floor beneath him.

He passes the doors -- PELL, VANCE, HOLLOWAY -- cut into the stone above each one. Nowhere in the building is his own name cut into anything.

INT. PELL SCIENCE HALL - B-WING DOORS - NIGHT

His ring opens every door in the building. One it does not: the wing posted for asbestos eight years ago and never touched.

INT. MAINTENANCE OFFICE - MORNING

The work order reads PREP B-WING FOR DEMO. Clipped beneath it is a key he has never been issued.

# ACT TWO

INT. B-WING - SEALED LAB - NIGHT

Behind the new drywall, the old doorframe is still there, painted over. The floor inside is a fresh sheet of grey.

He has painted the floor three times. Each morning the dark comes back up through the newest grey, a little east of where he centered it.

The drain backs up. He reaches past the trap and lifts out a student ID, swollen, the photo still readable. The name under it is MARA OKAFOR.

He knows the room by the way the mop drags. He worked it once, on overtime, signed for the hours, and never asked whose night it had been.

INT. MAINTENANCE OFFICE - DAY

His supervisor finds him at the time clock, sets a hand on his shoulder, mentions a raise.

SUPERVISOR
(easy, friendly)
Don't you worry about B-wing, Walt. Maintenance has that one covered now.

# ACT THREE

INT. B-WING - SEALED LAB - NIGHT

He stands over the dark shape with the roller loaded. For a long time, he does not move.

He sets the roller down in the tray and leaves the floor the way it is.

On his way out, he leaves the wing's lights burning.

INT. STAFF LOCKER ROOM - NIGHT

He tapes MARA OKAFOR's ID to locker 12, beside the strip with his own name -- the only two names in the building no one paid to carve.

EXT. CAMPUS GATE - DAY

Two weeks later, they collect his keys at the gate.

INT. PELL SCIENCE HALL - MAIN CORRIDOR - DAY

No one buffs that corridor again. The floor goes dull, and his face stops coming up in it.
